The {{Nihongo||金光教教典|'''Konkōkyō Kyōten'''|{{lit}} "Konkokyo Book of Teachings"|lead=yes}} is the main religious scripture of [[Konkokyo]], a [[Shinto]]-derived Japanese religion founded in 1859 by {{nihongo|[[Konkō Daijin]]|金光大神}} (1814–1883). ''Konkōkyō Kyōten'' is a compilation of various writings composed by Konkō Daijin and his disciples during the second half of the 19th century.<ref>{{cite web | title=Encyclopedia of Shinto | website=國學院大學デジタルミュージアム | url=https://d-museum.kokugakuin.ac.jp/eos/detail/?id=9816 | access-date=2025-06-05}}</ref>

==Contents==
The ''Konkōkyō Kyōten'' (金光教教典)<ref>{{cite web | title=金光教教典 | website=konkozaidan.jp | date=2009-04-28 | url=http://www.konkozaidan.jp/kyotosya/books/data_books/t1240898693/index_html | language=ja | access-date=2025-05-26}}</ref> is Konkokyo's primary scripture. It consists of three parts, of which the third part, ''Kyōten Gorikai'' (金光大神御理解集, "Teachings of Konko Daijin"), is the largest one.<ref>{{cite book |title=Shine from within: An introduction to the Konko Faith |author=Konkokyo |date=2009 |location=Konko, Okayama |publisher=Konkokyo |oclc=61459011}}</ref><ref name="konkokyo jp books"/>

#''Kyōten Konkō Daijin Oboegaki'' (金光大神御覚書, "Memoirs of Konko Daijin"): 25 chapters, which Konko Daijin began writing starting from November 23, 1874.
#''Kyōten Oshirase-goto Oboe-chō'' (お知らせ事覚帳, "Record of Revelations"): 27 chapters, one for each year from 1857 to 1883.
#''Kyōten Gorikai'' (金光大神御理解集, "Teachings of Konko Daijin"): This part, by far the largest one, consists of 3 volumes. It consists of Konkō Daijin's orally transmitted teachings as written down by his various disciples.
##Volume 1: 27 sections ordered according to the name of the disciple. There are 25 disciples total, since there are 3 sections for one of the disciples, {{nihongo|Ichimura Mitsugorō|市村光五郎|}}.
##Volume 2: 153 sections ordered according to the name of the disciple
##Volume 3: 8 sections
###{{nihongo|''Omichi Annai''|御道案内}}
###{{nihongo|''Shinkai''|慎誡}}
###{{nihongo|''Kyōso Gorikai''|教祖御理解}}
###{{nihongo|''Shinkun''|神訓}}
###{{nihongo|''Konkō Kyōso Gorikai''|金光教祖御理解}}
###{{nihongo|''Gorikai Shūi''|御理解拾遺}}
###{{nihongo|''Jinkyūkyō Goroku''|尋求教語録}}
###{{nihongo|''Naiden''|内伝}}

In addition to the main book, there are also the following supplemental volumes:<ref name="konkokyo jp books">{{cite web | title=書籍案内 | website=金光教公式サイト | date=2025-03-10 | url=https://www.konkokyo.jp/faith/teaching/books/ | language=ja | access-date=2025-05-06}}</ref>

*Index (用語索引)
*Announcements (お知らせ事覚書帳注釈) (annotated historical notices and memoranda)
*Biographical dictionary (人物誌)
*Glossary (用語事典)
*Supplement (追補) (122 verses of teachings that 12 followers had received from Konko Daijin)

==Editions==
There is a 1983 Japanese edition of the main volume of the ''Konkōkyō Kyōten'', as well as a more recent revised Japanese edition published in 2009. The English edition is published as 5 separate volumes:<ref>{{cite web | title=金光教教典 | website=金光教徒社 | date=2009-04-28 | url=http://www.konkozaidan.jp/kyotosya/books/data_books/t1240898693/index_html | language=ja | access-date=2025-06-05}}</ref>

*''Kyoten Konko Daijin Oboegaki: Memoirs of Konko Daijin'' (金光大神御覚書)
*''Kyoten Oshirase-goto Oboe-cho: Record of Revelations'' (お知らせ事覚帳)
*''Kyoten Gorikai: Teachings of Konko Daijin'' (金光大神御理解集) (3 volumes)

